# API OpenAPI Requirements

Every Flask endpoint under `app/api/` MUST have matching OpenAPI under `specs/api/` (`openapi.yml`, `paths/`, `schemas/`). If you edit serializers/response schemas, update specs so documented JSON matches the real response.

Per endpoint: method + path, summary, parameters, request body (if any), responses (200/201, 401, 422, 500), `security: [ bearerAuth: [] ]`, at least one example per response.

**Versioning**: For **new** endpoints, prefer `/api/v1/...` and versioned blueprints/modules; keep existing legacy paths until deliberate migration.

Validate before commit: `python scripts/validate_openapi.py` (or project equivalent).
